<title type="html"><![CDATA[9/12(Thu.)5 facts about sleeping/Climate crisis: Is travel writing still morally legitimate?(Host:Danny)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=316&amp;p=332#p332"><![CDATA[
9/12(Thu.) Sweet dreams are made of this: 5 facts about sleeping/Climate crisis: Is travel writing — or even travelling — still morally legitimate?(Host:Danny)<br /><br />Sweet dreams are made of this: 5 facts about sleeping<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://m.dw.com/en/sweet-dreams-are-made-of-this-5-facts-about-sleeping/a-44330691">https://m.dw.com/en/sweet-dreams-are-ma ... a-44330691</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. How many hours do you sleep per day?<br />2. Do you have any tip for sleep?<br />3. Have you had insomnia? Do you have any idea to deal with it.<br />4. Do you have any special story about dreams or sleep ?<br /><br />Climate crisis: Is travel writing — or even travelling — still morally legitimate?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.dw.com/en/climate-crisis-is-travel-writing-or-even-traveling-still-morally-legitimate/a-49969605">https://www.dw.com/en/climate-crisis-is ... a-49969605</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. Do you think it is a good idea to protect environment? Or just a fact issue.<br />2. In Taiwan, only way to go abroad is to take a plane.(Ship also can produce lots pollutants.) But we still can buy less export things. Do you think it possible? Or you can share your ideas to reduce pollution.<br />3. Many and many environment issues have been purpose in these years. Which part do you value most? (Ocean, ground, water...)<br /><br /><br />Suggested Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:30 p.m. free talk <br />7:30 p.m. --8:10 p.m. first topic discussion <br />8:10 p.m. --8:40 p.m. Presentation (All participants are invited)<br />8:40 p.m.-- 9.:15 p.m. second topic discussion <br />9:15 p.m.-- 9:30 p.m. Presentation<br /><br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Mon Sep 09, 2019 12:19 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
